and for Lewis P. Grinnan Jr., a dear friend, who allowed me to appreciate London."ô
ñDONATED ON BEHALF OF MR. AND MRS. A.F. CASTILLO
AMERICAN RESIDENTS OF LONDON
WHO HAVE ENJOYED FOR MANY YEARS
THE BEAUTY OF THE MOUNT STREET GARDENS"ö
óThe Sorbus tree in the North side of the garden
was planted in memory of
Sir Terence Rattigan, CBE (1911-1977)
by David Suchet CBE
on 22nd May 2012"û
